sentences.english: Let us have a look at New Jersey's pre-eminent University Town.
sentences.chinese: 讓我們看看新澤西出類拔萃的大學城。

sentences.english: I wish you every success in the future, You are worthysuccess.
sentences.chinese: 我祝你來日事業成功，出類拔萃，成功當之無愧。

sentences.english: For example: He [father] sent John to the university and was eager to have him distinguish himself.
sentences.chinese: 他送約翰上大學，巴望能讓兒子出類拔萃。

sentences.english: Aileen stands out for her incredible versatility as an actress.
sentences.chinese: 艾琳多才多藝，是一位出類拔萃的女演員。

sentences.english: In this field he is facile princeps, and has left all competitors behind.
sentences.chinese: 在這方面，他是出類拔萃的，使其他的競爭者。

sentences.english: Two CEO biogs stand out from the crowd.
sentences.chinese: 有兩家公司執行長的個人小傳出類拔萃。

sentences.english: Quality embodies dignity, An outstanding quality will not embrace any sort of mediocrity .
sentences.chinese: 品質體現尊嚴，出類拔萃的品質氣絕平庸。

sentences.english: Every day you have the chance to excel, to stand out, and to be exceptional.
sentences.chinese: 每天你都有機會勝人一籌，幹得出色，出類拔萃。

sentences.english: When I told him that i had superlatively technical skills, he simply gave me a horse laugh.
sentences.chinese: 當我告訴他我的技術出類拔萃時，他不相信地笑了。

sentences.english: This is for Plato, the political passion par excellence.
sentences.chinese: 那就是柏拉圖所謂的激情，出類拔萃的政治激情。

sentences.english: Reading great poets, I walked day and night in the shadow of excellence.
sentences.chinese: 常讀大詩人的作品，朝朝夕夕走在出類拔萃的影子裏。

sentences.english: From the beginning, it was evident that this boy was to be drawn to writing and the sound of words.
sentences.chinese: 這個孩子從一開始就表現出對寫作和聲韻的出類拔萃。

sentences.english: Professor Jao is also highly accomplished in the realm of the arts.
sentences.chinese: 饒教授在藝術領域亦取得出類拔萃的成就。
